# Quick Start Guide

### Download nf-interpreter source from github.

https://github.com/nanoframework/nf-interpreter

### Download Prerequisites

- [Visual Studio 2017](https://www.visualstudio.com/downloads/)
  - Install VS2017 including **Desktop development with C++** option for using nmake
- [gcc](https://developer.arm.com/open-source/gnu-toolchain/gnu-rm/downloads)
  - Install gcc-arm-none-eabi-6-2017-q2-update-win32.exe
- [CMake](https://cmake.org/download/)
  - Install cmake-3.8.2-win64-x64.msi
- [OpenOCD](http://gnutoolchains.com/arm-eabi/openocd/)
  - Download OpenOCD-20170609.zip and extract it. I extract it to D:/Backup/DevelopmentTools/OpenOCD-20170609.

### Download Visual Studio Code

- [Visual Studio Code](http://code.visualstudio.com/)
- [CMake Extension](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=twxs.cmake)
- [CMake Tools Extension](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=vector-of-bool.cmake-tools)


### Setup configuration files

##### Copy to .vscode/launch.json. 

Please check the path of below files.
- arm-none-eabi-gdb.exe : default path
- nanoBooter.hex
- nanoBooter.elf
- openocd.exe
- openocd script folder
- nanoCLR.hex
- nanoCLR.elf

```json
{
  "version": "0.2.0",
  "configurations": [
    {
      "name": "nanoBooter",
      "type": "cppdbg",
      "request": "launch",
      "miDebuggerPath": "C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools ARM Embedded/6 2017-q2-update/bin/arm-none-eabi-gdb.exe",
      "targetArchitecture": "ARM",
      "program": "${workspaceRoot}/build/nanoBooter.elf",

      "setupCommands": [
        { "text": "target extended-remote localhost:3333" },
        { "text": "monitor reset halt" },
        { "text": "monitor flash write_image erase \"c:/work/nf-interpreter/build/nanoBooter.hex\"" },
        { "text": "file c:/work/nf-interpreter/build/nanoBooter.elf" },
        { "text": "monitor reset halt" }
      ],

      "customLaunchSetupCommands": [
        { "text": "monitor reset halt" }
      ],

      "launchCompleteCommand": "exec-continue",
      "debugServerPath": "D:/Backup/DevelopmentTools/OpenOCD-20170609/bin/openocd.exe",
```

##### Copy to .vscode/settings.json

```json
{
    "cmake.generator": "NMake Makefiles",
    "files.associations": {
        "xlocale": "cpp",
        "system_error": "cpp",
        "istream": "cpp",
        "xutility": "cpp",
        "xmemory0": "cpp"
    }
}
```

### Build on VS Code

Open nf-interpreter folder using VS Code.

Click "Select a build environment..." on the bottom bar of VS Code.

<img src="data:image/png;base64," />

Select any environment for using nmake.

<img src="data:image/png;base64," />

Click to select current build type on the bottom bar of VS Code.

<img src="data:image/png;base64," />

Select the build type which you want.

<img src="data:image/png;base64," />

Now, it's ready to build.

<img src="data:image/png;base64," />

Click the Build button on the bottom bar.

<img src="data:image/png;base64," />

nanoBooter and nanoClr files are generated.

<img src="data:image/png;base64," />


### Write nf-interpreter to target board flash memory

Run below command for writing nf-interpreter to target board flash memory.

program.bat
```
@echo off
"C:\Program Files (x86)\STMicroelectronics\STM32 ST-LINK Utility\ST-LINK Utility\ST-LINK_CLI.exe" -c UR SWD -ME -V "while_programming" -p "build\nanoBooter.hex" -p "build\nanoClr.hex" -Rst
pause
```

After writing, you can see USB Serial Device on Device Manager.

<img src="data:image/png;base64," />

### Build nF Application

Open Visual Studio 2017.

Open New Project window in File -> New -> Project menu.

![New Project Window](data:image/png;base64,)

If you cannot find nF templates, please make sure .NET Framework version is 4.6 or above in New Project window.


### Debug nf-interpreter

Click the Debug menu on the left.

![Debug Menu](data:image/png;base64,)

Choose your target, nanoBooter or nanoCLR.

![Target](data:image/png;base64,)

Click Start Debugging button

![Button](data:image/png;base64,)
